<h3>Background</h3>
<p>
BION meta is an open source package for microbiome analyses, but 
only 16S/18S rRNA works yet. This sheet, which can be given to anyone,
summarizes its current status,
<p>
<a href="BION_meta.pdf">BION_meta.pdf</a>
</p>
<p>
In brief, as of spring 2013 it is in some ways better than Qiime/Mothur,
but lacks statistics and figures. The features to be added will however
make BION tops in every aspect, we think 
(see the <a href="BION.todo.html">to-do list</a>).
</p>
<p>
Development focus is on more accurate results, shorter run-times, 
more transparent results and access, and on making it easy for 
inexperienced users to run and re-run flows. The aim is a package that 
scales really well with very many datasets and is as convenient as can
be, with little manual intervention.
</p>
<p>
The package will remain 100% open source, because hiding analysis 
logic is black-box science and this will not be popular with journals
in the future. Requiring a proprietary license also works as a barrier 
for reproducing results. So do difficult-to-use open source packages, 
but BION tries to address that (e.g. complete installation is done with
"./install_software --all" on any Linux, Unix or Mac system).
</p>
