<h3>License</h3>
<p>
The BION package uses the <a href="http://www.gnu.org/licenses/gpl.html">
GNU Public License v3</a>. The package includes many general open-source 
packages and libraries that each have their open source license, but they
all allow free running and sharing. The BION package may be used in house,
commercially or not, and to provide free services as well. The only limit
is for customer paid services, which requires a revenue-sharing agreement. 
</p>
<h3>Services</h3>
<p>
We can run data through remotely and help customers interpret their data,
for example. By offering our services, entities not normally in the analysis
business can earn income merely by giving us remote data access providing 
a modest off-shelf computer resource. Thus entities do not need to hire 
and train personnel, or can free personnel for other purposes. See also 
our other services above.
</p>
